India  and Pakistan will resume
playing cricket and hockey matches after bilateral series
between the two nations were suspended in the wake of the Mumbai
terrorist attacks, the Indian Express  reported .  The Indian cricket team will tour Pakistan early next year
to play Test and one-day matches, the newspaper said, citing
government sources that it didnâ€™t identify. The hockey teams
will play matches in India later this year, the Express said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
